@owner: TrellisProject
@stability: stable
@since: 2026-05-09
@reviewed: 2026-05-10
@allow-many-consumes: "AST-to-Sidecar projection adapter; per-method coupling to tree-sitter's Node API is the binding's surface, not this file's design — the alternative is a wrapper-of-a-wrapper that adds no value"

Feature: AST Projection
  "Walks a parsed Trellis tree and materializes the Sidecar fields the graph cares about."

  Provides:
    - graph.Extract

  Consumes:
    - sitter.Tree
    - sitter.Node
    - graph.Sidecar
    - graph.Entry
    - graph.Handle
    - graph.HandleKind
    - graph.SourcePathFor

  Invariants:
    - Extract MUST NOT be called on a tree where HasError() is true — the parser is the source of truth for shape
    - Extract SHALL produce only the Provides and Consumes lists; other context blocks are linter territory
    - Description text MUST be preserved verbatim (whitespace-trimmed) and never interpreted
    - Extract SHOULD silently skip AST nodes it does not recognize, on the principle that the grammar may extend without breaking the extractor

  OutOfScope:
    - Frontmatter parsing (separate concern)
    - Scenario / step extraction (linter)
    - Recovery from partial / error trees (responsibility of the caller)
    - Per-language description-field validation

  Scenario (happy-path): PathHandle entry with description
    Given a handle_entry whose handle is path_handle 'Subscription.create' with trailing description
    When Extract processes the surrounding tree
    Then the Sidecar's Provides slice contains an Entry with Handle.Path='Subscription.create' and a non-empty Description

  Scenario (happy-path): PrefixedHandle entry
    Given a handle_entry whose handle is prefixed_handle Event:subscription.created
    When Extract processes the tree
    Then the Sidecar's Provides slice contains an Entry with Kind=PrefixedHandle, Prefix='Event', Path='subscription.created'

  Scenario (negative): Tree without a feature node
    Given a tree whose root has no 'feature' field
    When Extract is called
    Then it returns an error mentioning 'no feature'

  Scenario (edge): Empty Provides block (no entries)
    Given a feature with a Provides: block that has zero handle_entries (parser-impossible today, but tolerable)
    When Extract is called
    Then the resulting Sidecar.Provides slice is nil or empty (no panic)
